ITINewsDescriptopn: The forum was attended by Dr. Amr Talaat, Minister of Communications and Information Technology, Dr. Heba Saleh, President of the Information Technology Institute, Dr. Ahmed Khattab, President of the National Telecommunications Institute, and representatives of the partners of the “Jefa-Tech” initiative from both Nasser Social Bank and employment partners. There are also examples of new partners joining the initiative this year, and examples of success and excellence stories from the initiative’s youth. Dr. Amr Talaat pointed out in his speech that building digital capabilities is one of the strategic axes of the Ministry of Communications and Information Technology, with the aim of qualifying young people from various specializations and academic backgrounds, and enhancing their competitive capabilities in the labor market.
ITIAd1: Applications are open for the E-mobility program in cooperation with Brightskies
ITIAd2: Opening of registration for the (TECH AMBASSADORS) Program

ITIAdDes1: The Information Technology Institute (ITI), affiliated with the Ministry of Communications and Information Technology, announced the launch of the (E-mobility) program, with the aim of qualifying a number of specialists in this field and meeting the growing market needs for it. This comes in cooperation with Brightskies, a leading company in providing technological solutions for digital transformation that are compatible with the needs of the business environment of the communications and information technology sector.
ITIAdDes2: Dr. Heba Saleh, President of the Information Technology Institute (ITI), said that the program aims to train a limited number of graduates of engineering colleges or their equivalent on E-mobility technologies. Through the program in its first phase, the Institute aims to train graduates of engineering colleges and their equivalents in the following departments only: electrical power - electromechanical engineering - electronics engineering - mechatronics engineering - computer engineering. Dr. added. Heba Saleh, President of the Information Technology Institute (ITI), said that the duration of the training will be more than 400 training hours covering the fields (power electronics, electric vehicle systems, basics of embedded systems).
